teLinkMIB.description: Copyright (C) 2003 The Internet Society. This version of this MIB module is part of RFCXXXX; see the RFC itself for full legal notices. This MIB module contains managed object definitions for MPLS traffic engineering links as defined in 'Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering'.

Priority.name: Priority
Priority.description: This type is used to represent a priority. Each connection is assigned a priority. This priority is used when accounting for bandwidth on TE links or component links, for resource allocation and for rerouting purposes. Value 0 is the highest priority. Value 7 is the lowest priority.

SwitchingCapability.name: SwitchingCapability
SwitchingCapability.description: Switching capability as specified in the 'OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS' document. The values specified in this document are not contiguous.

LinkEncodingType.name: LinkEncodingType
LinkEncodingType.description: Link encoding type as specified in 'GMPLS Signaling Functional Description' document. The values specified in this document are not contiguous.

teLinkTable.name: teLinkTable
teLinkTable.description: This table specifies the grouping of component links into TE links and grouping of TE links into bundled links.

teLinkEntry.name: teLinkEntry
teLinkEntry.description: An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of teLink(200), i.e. for every TE link. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkEntry is created with the corresponding ifIndex. If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so is the corresponding entry in the teLinkTable. The administrative and operational status values are controlled from the ifEntry.

teLinkAddressType.name: teLinkAddressType
teLinkAddressType.description: The type of Internet address for the TE link. Only IPv4, IPv6 and unknown (for unnumbered links) need to be supported.

teLinkLocalIpAddr.name: teLinkLocalIpAddr
teLinkLocalIpAddr.description: For IPv4 and IPv6 numbered links, this object represents the local IP address associated with the TE link. For unnumbered link, the local address is not stored in this object, but rather in the teLinkOutgoingIfId object.

teLinkRemoteIpAddr.name: teLinkRemoteIpAddr
teLinkRemoteIpAddr.description: The remote IP address associated with the TE link (IPv4 and IPv6 numbered links). For unnumbered links, the remote address is not stored in this object, but rather in the teLinkIncomingIfId object.

teLinkMetric.name: teLinkMetric
teLinkMetric.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering, RFC xxxx
teLinkMetric.description: The traffic engineering metric for the TE link is derived from its component links. All component links within the TE link must have the same traffic engineering metric.

teLinkMuxCapability.name: teLinkMuxCapability
teLinkMuxCapability.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
teLinkMuxCapability.description: This attribute specifies link multiplex capability of the TE link, which is derived from its component links. All component links within the same TE link must have the same link multiplex capability.

teLinkProtectionType.name: teLinkProtectionType
teLinkProtectionType.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx and Routing Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
teLinkProtectionType.description: This attribute specifies link protection type of the TE link. Description of the different protection types can be found in the 'Routing Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS' document.

teLinkWorkingPriority.name: teLinkWorkingPriority
teLinkWorkingPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
teLinkWorkingPriority.description: This object represents a priority value such that a new connection with a higher priority, i.e. numerically lower than this value, is guaranteed to be setup on a primary link and not on a secondary link.

teLinkResourceClass.name: teLinkResourceClass
teLinkResourceClass.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering, RFC xxxx and Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC xxxx
teLinkResourceClass.description: This attribute specifies the TE link resource class. The resource class is a 32 bit bitfield. The resource class for a link bundle is derived from the resource class of its TE links. All TE links within a link bundle must have the same resource class. Encoding of the resource class is described in the 'Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 2' document.

teLinkIncomingIfId.name: teLinkIncomingIfId
teLinkIncomingIfId.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering, RFC xxxx
teLinkIncomingIfId.description: For unnumbered links, the incoming interface is set to the outgoing interface identifier chosen by the neighboring LSR for the reverse link corresponding to this TE link. For numbered links, the address is stored in the teLinkRemoteIpAddr instead.

teLinkOutgoingIfId.name: teLinkOutgoingIfId
teLinkOutgoingIfId.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering, RFC xxxx
teLinkOutgoingIfId.description: If the link is unnumbered, the outgoing interface identifier is set to the outgoing interface identifier chosen for the TE link by the advertising LSR. For numbered links, the address is stored in the teLinkLocalIpAddr instead.

teLinkRowStatus.name: teLinkRowStatus
teLinkRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. All read-create objects can only be changed when teLinkRowStatus is notInService(2) or notReady(3).

teLinkStorageType.name: teLinkStorageType
teLinkStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkDescriptorTable.name: teLinkDescriptorTable
teLinkDescriptorTable.description: This table specifies the link descriptors associated with the TE links.

teLinkDescriptorEntry.name: teLinkDescriptorEntry
teLinkDescriptorEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every TE link descriptor. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkDescriptorEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifType of ifEntry must be teLink(200). If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the teLinkDescriptorTable that use the ifIndex of this TE link.

teLinkDescriptorId.name: teLinkDescriptorId
teLinkDescriptorId.description: This object specifies the link descriptor identifier.

teLinkDescrEncodingType.name: teLinkDescrEncodingType
teLinkDescrEncodingType.reference: Generalized MPLS Signaling Functional Description, RFC 3471
teLinkDescrEncodingType.description: This attribute specifies the TE link encoding type.

teLinkDescrPriority.name: teLinkDescrPriority
teLinkDescrPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
teLinkDescrPriority.description: This object specifies the lowest priority at which that link encoding type is available.

teLinkDescrMinResBandwidth.name: teLinkDescrMinResBandwidth
teLinkDescrMinResBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
teLinkDescrMinResBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the minimum reservable bandwidth on the TE link. This is derived from the union of the minimum reservable bandwidth of all the component links associated with the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic. This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

teLinkDescrMaxResBandwidth.name: teLinkDescrMaxResBandwidth
teLinkDescrMaxResBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
teLinkDescrMaxResBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the maximum reservable bandwidth on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum reservable bandwidth of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic. This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

teLinkDescrRowStatus.name: teLinkDescrRowStatus
teLinkDescrRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can changed if teLinkDescrRowStatus is in active(1) state.

teLinkDescrStorageType.name: teLinkDescrStorageType
teLinkDescrStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkDescriptorTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkSrlgTable.name: teLinkSrlgTable
teLinkSrlgTable.description: This table specifies the SRLGs associated with TE links.

teLinkSrlgEntry.name: teLinkSrlgEntry
teLinkSrlgEntry.description: An entry in this table contains information about a SRLG associated with a TE link. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkSrlgEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifType of ifEntry must be teLink(200). If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the teLinkSrlgTable that use the ifIndex of this TE link.

srlg.name: srlg
srlg.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
srlg.description: This identifies a SRLG supported by the TE link. An SRLG is identified with a 32 bit number that is unique within an IGP domain. Zero is a valid SRLG number.

srlgRowStatus.name: srlgRowStatus
srlgRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified if srlgRowStatus is active(1).

srlgStorageType.name: srlgStorageType
srlgStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkSrlgTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkBandwidthTable.name: teLinkBandwidthTable
teLinkBandwidthTable.description: This table specifies the priority-based bandwidth table for TE links.

teLinkBandwidthEntry.name: teLinkBandwidthEntry
teLinkBandwidthEntry.description: An entry in this table contains information about the priority-based bandwidth of TE links. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkBandwidthEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifType of ifEntry must be teLink(200). If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the teLinkBandwidthTable that use the ifIndex of this TE link.

teLinkPriority.name: teLinkPriority
teLinkPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx and Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC xxxx
teLinkPriority.description: This attribute specifies the priority. A value of 0 is valid as specified in the 'Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 2' document.

teLinkUnreservedBandwidth.name: teLinkUnreservedBandwidth
teLinkUnreservedBandwidth.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering, RFC xxxx
teLinkUnreservedBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the TE link unreserved bandwidth at priority p. It is the sum of the unreserved bandwidths at priority p of all component links associated with the TE link (excludes all links that are strictly used as protecting links). This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

teLinkMaximumLspBandwidth.name: teLinkMaximumLspBandwidth
teLinkMaximumLspBandwidth.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering, RFC xxxx
teLinkMaximumLspBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the TE link maximum LSP bandwidth at priority p. It is the maximum of all maximum LSP bandwidth at priority p of the component links associated with the TE link (excludes all links that are strictly used as protecting links). This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

teLinkBandwidthRowStatus.name: teLinkBandwidthRowStatus
teLinkBandwidthRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified when teLinkBandwidthRowStatus is active(1).

teLinkBandwidthStorageType.name: teLinkBandwidthStorageType
teLinkBandwidthStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkBandwidthTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

componentLinkTable.name: componentLinkTable
componentLinkTable.description: This table specifies the component link parameters.

componentLinkEntry.name: componentLinkEntry
componentLinkEntry.description: An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry that represents a component link. An ifEntry must exist in the ifTable before a componentLinkEntry is created with the corresponding ifIndex. ifEntry's ifType can be of any interface type which has been defined for TE Link interworking. Examples include ATM, Frame Relay, Ethernet, etc. If an entry representing a component link is destroyed in the ifTable, then so is the corresponding entry in the componentLinkTable. The administrative and operational status values are controlled from the ifEntry.

componentLinkMuxCapability.name: componentLinkMuxCapability
componentLinkMuxCapability.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
componentLinkMuxCapability.description: This attribute specifies link multiplexing capabilities of the component link.

componentLinkPreferredProtection.name: componentLinkPreferredProtection
componentLinkPreferredProtection.description: This attribute specifies whether this component link is a primary or secondary entity.

componentLinkCurrentProtection.name: componentLinkCurrentProtection
componentLinkCurrentProtection.description: This attribute specifies whether this component link is currently used as primary or secondary link.

componentLinkRowStatus.name: componentLinkRowStatus
componentLinkRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified when componentLinkRowStatus is active(1).

componentLinkStorageType.name: componentLinkStorageType
componentLinkStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the componentLinkTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

componentLinkDescriptorTable.name: componentLinkDescriptorTable
componentLinkDescriptorTable.description: This table specifies the link descriptors associated with the component links.

componentLinkDescriptorEntry.name: componentLinkDescriptorEntry
componentLinkDescriptorEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every component link descriptor. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a componentLinkDescriptorEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifEntry's ifType can be of any interface type which has been defined for TE Link interworking. Examples include ATM, Frame Relay, Ethernet, etc. If a component link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the componentLinkDescriptorTable that use the ifIndex of this component link.

componentLinkDescrId.name: componentLinkDescrId
componentLinkDescrId.description: This object specifies the link descriptor identifier.

componentLinkDescrEncodingType.name: componentLinkDescrEncodingType
componentLinkDescrEncodingType.reference: Generalized MPLS Signaling Functional Description, RFC 3471
componentLinkDescrEncodingType.description: This attribute specifies the component link encoding type.

componentLinkDescrPriority.name: componentLinkDescrPriority
componentLinkDescrPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
componentLinkDescrPriority.description: This object specifies the lowest priority at which that link encoding type is available for the component link.

componentLinkDescrMinBandwidth.name: componentLinkDescrMinBandwidth
componentLinkDescrMinBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
componentLinkDescrMinBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the minimum reservable bandwidth on the component link. This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

componentLinkDescrMaxBandwidth.name: componentLinkDescrMaxBandwidth
componentLinkDescrMaxBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
componentLinkDescrMaxBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the maximum reservable bandwidth on the component link. This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

componentLinkDescrRowStatus.name: componentLinkDescrRowStatus
componentLinkDescrRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified when componentLinkDescrRowStatus is active(1).

componentLinkDescrStorageType.name: componentLinkDescrStorageType
componentLinkDescrStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the componentLinkDescriptorTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

componentLinkBandwidthTable.name: componentLinkBandwidthTable
componentLinkBandwidthTable.description: This table specifies the priority-based bandwidth for component links.

componentLinkBandwidthEntry.name: componentLinkBandwidthEntry
componentLinkBandwidthEntry.description: An entry in this table contains information about the priority-based bandwidth on component links. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a componentLinkBandwidthEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifEntry's ifType can be of any interface type which has been defined for TE Link interworking. Examples include ATM, Frame Relay, Ethernet, etc. If a component link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the componentLinkBandwidthTable that use the ifIndex of this component link.

componentLinkPriority.name: componentLinkPriority
componentLinkPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx and Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC xxxx
componentLinkPriority.description: This attribute specifies the priority. A value of 0 is valid as specified in the 'Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 2' document.

componentLinkUnreservedBandwidth.name: componentLinkUnreservedBandwidth
componentLinkUnreservedBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
componentLinkUnreservedBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the component link unreserved bandwidth at priority p. This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

componentLinkMaximumLspBandwidth.name: componentLinkMaximumLspBandwidth
componentLinkMaximumLspBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized MPLS, RFC xxxx
componentLinkMaximumLspBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the component link maximum LSP bandwidth at priority p. This value is an estimate in units of 1,000 bits per second.

componentLinkBandwidthRowStatus.name: componentLinkBandwidthRowStatus
componentLinkBandwidthRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified when componentLinkBandwidthRowStatus is active(1).

componentLinkBwStorageType.name: componentLinkBwStorageType
componentLinkBwStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the componentLinkBandwidthTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkNotificationsEnabled.name: teLinkNotificationsEnabled
teLinkNotificationsEnabled.description: If this object is true, then it enables the generation of the TE link notifications, otherwise these notifications are not emitted.

linkBundleMismatch.name: linkBundleMismatch
linkBundleMismatch.description: This notification is generated when a mismatch is found on a bundled link. Such mismatch can be detected for instance if one of the traffic engineering parameters is not consistent across all TE links within a bundled link (resource class, etc.).

teLinkModuleFullCompliance.name: teLinkModuleFullCompliance
teLinkModuleFullCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents that support the configuration and monitoring of TE Link MIB module.

teLinkModuleReadOnlyCompliance.name: teLinkModuleReadOnlyCompliance
teLinkModuleReadOnlyCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents that support the monitoring of TE link MIB module.

teLinkGroup.name: teLinkGroup
teLinkGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for the monitoring of resources associated with TE links.

teLinkSrlgGroup.name: teLinkSrlgGroup
teLinkSrlgGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for the monitoring of SRLG resources associated with TE links.

teLinkBandwidthGroup.name: teLinkBandwidthGroup
teLinkBandwidthGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for the monitoring of the priority-based bandwidth resources associated with TE links and component links.

componentLinkBandwidthGroup.name: componentLinkBandwidthGroup
componentLinkBandwidthGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for the monitoring of bandwidth parameters associated with component links.

teLinkNotificationGroup.name: teLinkNotificationGroup
teLinkNotificationGroup.description: Set of notifications implemented in this module. None is mandatory.
